olive oil
1 carrot
1 bag green beans
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
½ packet Currants
¾ cup boiling water
1 packet pork mince
1 packet tomato paste
½ cup water
1 bag salad leaves
½ lemon
1 packet Moroccan Curry Paste
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Boil the kettle. Grate the carrot. Trim green beans and cut into thirds.
• In a medium heatproof bowl, place couscous, chicken-style stock powder
and currants (see ingredients).
• Add the boiling water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 1 1/2 cups for 4 people) and stir
to combine. Immediately cover with a plate and leave for 5 minutes.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook pork mince, carrot and green beans, breaking mince
up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-6 minutes.
• Add Moroccan curry paste and tomato paste and cook until fragrant,
1 minute.
• Add the water and cook until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes. Season
to taste.

• While the pork is cooking, fluff up couscous with a fork.
• Add salad leaves. Stir to combine and season with salt and pepper.

• Slice lemon into wedges.
• Divide currant couscous between bowls. Top with Moroccan-style pork and
green beans.
• Serve with Greek-style yoghurt and lemon wedges.